modules.description: Provides logging with conditional formatting and grouping, supporting string and function-based messages. Operates on log policies, options, and arbitrary values to control output behavior. Used to instrument code with structured logs, conditionally execute logging, and organize related messages into groups.

Provides functions to parse and render templates using Shopify's Liquid syntax, including variable substitution and control structures. Works with strings representing template content and associative data structures for context. Used to generate dynamic HTML or text outputs based on predefined templates and input data.

provides structured logging with conditional formatting and grouping, operating on log policies and arbitrary values to control output. supports string and function-based messages, enabling code instrumentation, conditional logging, and message organization. allows developers to manage log verbosity, filter outputs, and group related events for clarity. examples include logging error conditions with context, conditionally emitting debug information, and aggregating related actions into logical units.
